snippet: Fan Yilin of China, Viktoria Komova of Russia and Daria Spiridonova and Madison Kocian of the United States tied for the top spot in the uneven bars finals at the world gymnastics championships in Glasgow.
abstract: Uneven bars final at world gymnastics championships ends in four-way tie between Fan Yilin of China, Viktoria Komova of Russia and Daria Spiridonova and Madison Kocian of United States.
lead_paragraph: Fan Yilin of China, Viktoria Komova of Russia and Daria Spiridonova and Madison Kocian of the United States tied for the top spot in the uneven bars finals at the world gymnastics championships in Glasgow.
